tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review:
I was visiting Mumbai from Delhi and the climate change caused my babies to catch a severe cold. Visited Dr Shetty based on his practo ratings and I wasnt disappointed at all. He was extremely friendly and very good with both infants and their parents. He takes time out to explain the ailment as well as the medication, is very helpful. I was initially surprised at the number of medications prescribed but the relief from these medicines was immediate. 
Only negative being his crowded clinic- Be prepared to wait for a while

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: Now my daughter is feeling good and no pimples on her head but still somewhat pimples is there on her forehead. From yesterday only I have started treatment so I will wait 2-3 days for complete recovery of pimples from her forehead. Thank you doctor. I am so thankful to you because 2 years back because of this problem only I went back to Karnataka with my daughter. Now after 2 years we came back to Bombay but again my daughter is same pimples problem on her head, around neck and on her face but now she is feeling good. Thank you so much doctor. I will wait for complete cure.

Overall  we  are happy  with the doctor. Although at first  we were surprised at the long list of medicines, the child has definitely benefitted With  the medication.  we  are satisfied. 

Reception area needs to be managed better. They seem to be overwhelmed with the crowd and can try to do better with attending at the reception. 

Also with the Doctor's cabin being open at all times there is a lot of interference from outside when a patient is attended to. This also can be improved with a closed cabin during patient appointment and the reception being responsible for managing entry and exit.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review:
Am very satisfied with the doctor's gesture towards parents and kids. My daughter had infection and I was tired and day by day it was getting triggered. I visited doctor Yuvraj and am so satisfied with his treatment as her allergy completely disappeared within a week.
He explains each and every parent with patience. 
He infact returned a call in case of emergency. I really appreciate the kindness of the doctor.

He looks good and friendly doctor, however prescribes too many medicines and vaccines for babies which are too costly. Also whatever medicines he writes are available only at the shop outside his clinic and only that chemist is able to read his medicines. I tried at 4-5 pharmacy shops as well as few online websites but most of his prescribed medicine were either non readable or not available.
Also everytime you visit him he charges followup consultation fees even if you go for vaccination which other pediatricians are not charging. ******* ** ** * **** ****** *** I feel he should lower the price as well as quantity of medicines and vaccines so that common people can afford. For people who don't bother for high price ** ** **** *******

Dr. Shetty has been extremely friendly & polite during every visit. He has a knack of engaging children when he is checking them. Every time we have received detailed instructions and he explains well. Seeks confirmation to check if the instructions are understood by us. He is always reachable even after business hours. The staff is also very cooperative and helpful.

We are really happy with our doctor. The personal attention and follow up from doctor and his team is really helpful to monitor the health and the vaccination routine. He patiently handles the infants and addresses parents concerns with utmost care and importance. Appreciate his committment

The doctor arrived 2 hours late.Also I was not informed about the correct consultation charge. my son was administered an immunity booster which was very expensive and was not informed about that cost too..I had to pay a huge fee at the time of leaving..The doctor seemed to be on a hurry and he also spoke rudely to my son..
